> # First let us visualize the data using boxplots
> myboxplot <- function(dataframe, x, y) {
+   dataframe %>%
+     dplyr::filter(!is.na({{x}}), !is.na({{y}})) %>%
+     ggplot(aes(fill = {{x}}, x = {{x}}, y = {{y}})) +
+     theme_classic() +
+     geom_boxplot() +
+     theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
+     theme(
+       plot.title = element_text(color = "black", size = 12, hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
+       axis.title.x = element_text(color = "black", size = 12, face = "bold"),
+       axis.title.y = element_text(color = "black", size = 12, face = "bold")
+     ) +
+     theme(axis.text = element_text(color = "black", size = 10)) +
+     theme(
+       legend.title = element_text(colour = "black", size = 16),
+       legend.position = "none",
+       legend.text = element_text(colour = "black", size = 14)
+     ) +
+     guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Generations")) +
+     stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = "line", aes(group = 1)) +
+     stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = "point")
+ }

> 
> for (generation in generations) {
+   subset_data <- dataset_dba[dataset_dba$Generation == generation, ]

+   mean_value <- round(mean(subset_data$Yield, na.rm = TRUE), 2)
+   
+   hist(subset_data$Yield, prob = TRUE, xlab = "Yield",
+        main = paste("Histogram and Density curve of Yield of", generation),

+ }

Accuracy and heritability

> lambda = sum.m5[grep('fa1',rownames(sum.m5)),1]
> psi = diag(sum.m5[grep('var',rownames(sum.m5)),1])
> Gvcov = lambda %*% t(lambda) + psi
> expvar1 = (sum(diag(lambda %*% t(lambda)))/
+              sum(diag(lambda %*% t(lambda) + psi)))*100
> 
> gencorrFA = cov2cor(Gvcov)

> acc.m5 = NULL
> her.m5 = NULL
> for(i in 1:nlevels(dataset_nodba$Generation)){
+   pred_vcov = predict(M5, classify = "Genotype:Generation",
+                       level=list(Generation = i), vcov = T)
+   pred_sed = predict(M5, classify = "Genotype:Generation",
+                      level=list(Generation = i), sed = T)
+   pred_sed$pvals 
+   PEV = mean(diag(pred_vcov$vcov))
+   mvd = mean((pred_sed$sed^2)[upper.tri(pred_sed$sed^2,diag = F)])
+   acc.m5[i] = sqrt(1-(PEV/Gvcov[i,i]))
+   her.m5[i] = 1-(mvd/(2*Gvcov[i,i]))
+ }
